                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Wikipedia explains Euler's Identity as a fundamental mathematical equation that relates five of the most important constants in mathematics: 0, 1, π, e, and i. It is expressed as:\n\n\\[ e^{i\\pi} + 1 = 0 \\]\n\nThis identity is a special case of Euler's formula \\( e^{ix} = \\cos x + i \\sin x \\) when \\( x = \\pi \\). It is celebrated for its beauty because it combines these constants and the fundamental operations of addition, multiplication, and exponentiation into a single, elegant formula that is considered a deep and profound connection in mathematics【4:0†source】.",
